{"word":"ἄψαυστος","slug":"ἄψαυστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄψαυστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ψαύω'><el>ψαύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>untouched, not to be touched, sacred</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>not touching</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}